    "And so, Jonah stood up and faced the city of Nineveh.",
    "He looked at the people, their faces filled with hope and joy.",
    "He looked at the animals, once destined for slaughter, now living in peace and harmony.",
    "And he realized that God's mercy was enough.",
    "As Jonah sat under his makeshift shelter, watching the city of Nineveh, he realized that God's mercy was not just enough, it was everything."
